gomodel:SYNGO_2904  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Expression of PIP5Kγ661 in Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"Like postsynaptic density 95 (PSD-95) and filamentous actin (F-actin), which were concentrated in the dendritic spines, endogenous PIP5Kγ661 was enriched in dendritic spine-like protrusions (see Figures S1A-S1E available online). Endogenous PIP5Kγ661 partially colocalized with PSD-95 and F-actin (Figures 1D and 1E). Furthermore, immunoblot analysis of the subcellular fractions of adult mouse brain showed PIP5Kγ661 not only in the SV fraction, which was immunonegative for PSD-95, but also in the PSD fractions, which were immunonegative for an SV marker synaptophysin (Figure 1F). Together, these results indicate that PIP5Kγ661 localizes at least in part to postsynapses.\". Experimental description: - \"Culture of Hippocampal Neurons and Transfection: Hippocampi dissected from E16/17 ICR mice ...\"\n- \"Electrophysiology: Transverse hippocampal slices (300 μm thickness) were prepared from P14-21 ICR mice ...\"\n- Overexpressed PIP5Kγ; Pip5k1c was of mouse species. Traced back to PMID:17290217: \"To construct Flag- and Myc-tagged mammalian expression vectors for PIP5Kα, PIP5Kβ, PIP5Kγ635 and PIP5Kγ661, cDNAs were amplified from mouse brain total RNA using RT-PCR,..\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2904" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

